    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hi @ahennie, thanks for your question! :)\n\nIt's not possible with dynamic facets (computed from the result set by the Algolia engine). However if you've extracted the facets on your side, it should be possible to create a custom widget for that. This widget could have the knowledge of all the facets that are in the dataset, and if the engine doesn't return a value, it will set the count to 0. The only drawback is that any new value for the facet mean an update in the frontend.\n\nWould that fit your need?\n",
